# rule.require.explicit-stdin-flags

stdin inputs must be explicitly declared via flags like `--reason @stdin`, never implicitly consumed.

## .why

implicit stdin = magic behavior: surprises users, breaks composability, hides contract.

## .pattern

```bash
# bad
echo "reason" | rhx goal.set --slug foo

# good
echo "reason" | rhx goal.set --slug foo --reason @stdin
```

## .enforcement

implicit stdin consumption = **BLOCKER**
